	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Mar 27th 8:50 AM</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.90]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>If you chat with Baobob long enough he mentions his sister making armor also, basically you tell chanda that, "baobob sent me" and she gives you the line with the keywords for each of the items.  "What boots", "What belt" and "what cloak" got me the rest of the info from her.  If there are people camping the millers most of them will allow you time to get an item or two from these quests if you just ask nicely.  Karana Residents is the faction you need, it goes up when you do the quests.  I was able to get boots and belts at apprehensive and the cloaks at indifferent (use sneak or benovelance/alliance or charasmatic carrilion if you have any of these) but if you don't have the faction for cloaks then getting a bunch of belts or boots will eventually raise your faction.  The bearhide armor is nice because it is better than leather and raw silk and the same AC as ringmail and any class/race can wear this stuff.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
